04) SIMPLE STATIC WEBSITE :
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Simple Website</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }
        header {
            background-color: #333;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        nav {
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            padding: 10px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        nav a {
            text-decoration: none;
            color: #333;
            padding: 10px;
        }
        nav a:hover {
            background-color: #ddd;
        }
        section {
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        footer {
            background-color: #333;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
    <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>
</header>

<nav>
    <a href="#">Home</a>
    <a href="#">About</a>
    <a href="#">Contact</a>
</nav>

<section>
    <h2>About Us</h2>
    <p>This is a simple static website.</p>
</section>

<footer>
    <p>&copy; 2024 My Website. All rights reserved.</p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>


05) CASCADING STYLE SHEET â€“ INLINE , INTERNAL , EXTERNAL

html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>CSS Example</title>


    <!-- External CSS -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">


    <!-- Internal CSS -->
    <style>
        h1 {
            color: green;
        }
        p {
            font-size: 16px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>


    <!-- Inline CSS -->
    <h1 style="color: blue;">This is a heading with inline CSS</h1>
    <p>This is a paragraph with internal CSS</p>
    <p class="external-css">This is another paragraph with external CSS</p>
</body>
</html>


And here's the content of the styles.css file:

css
.external-css {
    font-style: italic;
}






07) SHAWDOW AND TEXT EFFECTS :
<html>
<head>
<style>
.shadow{
 width:200px;
 height:100px;
 background-color:#f0f0f0;
 box-shadow:5px 5px 10px rgba(0,0,0.5);
 margin-bottom:20px;
 }
 
.shadow-2{
 box-shadow:-5px -5px 10px rgba(0,0,0.5); /*inset shadow*/
 }
 
.shadow-3{
 box-shadow:0 0 10px 5px rgba(0,0,255,0.5);/*spread shadow*/
 }
 
 .text-effects{
 text-shadow:2px 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
 letter-spacing:2px;
 }
 
 .colorful-text{
 color:#ff6f61;
 text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(255,111,97,0.5);
 }
 
 .shadow-container{
 width:300px;
 height:200px;
 background-color:#f0f0f0;
 box-shadow:5px 5px 10px rgba(0,0,0.5);
 margin-bottom:20px;
 }
 
 </style>
 </head>
 <body>
 <div class="shadow"></div>
 <div class="shadow shadow-2"></div>
 <div class="shadow shadow-3"></div>
 <p class="text-effects"> EFFECTS </p>
 <p class="colorful-text"> COLORFUL </p>
 <div class="shadow-container">
 <img class="image-inside-shadow" src="image4.jpg" alt="example image">
 </div>
 </body>
 </html>


















08) RESPONSIVE DESIGNS USING MEDIA QUERIES 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Responsive Design</title>
<style>
  /* Default styles */
  .container {
    width: 100%; /* Full width by default */
    padding: 20px;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  /* Media query for screens larger than 768px */
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .container {
      width: 50%; /* Change width to 50% on larger screens */
      margin: 0 auto; /* Center the container horizontally */
    }
  }

  /* Media query for screens larger than 1200px */
  @media (min-width: 1200px) {
    .container {
      width: 30%; /* Change width to 30% on even larger screens */
    }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">
  <p>This is a responsive container.</p>
</div>

</body>
</html>




